# Mobile Cursor → Railway deploy

Production deploys only from **`main`** (GitHub Actions → Railway + Cloudflare).

Cursor Mobile / cloud agents push to **`cursor/*` branches** and often open **draft PRs**. Those do **not** appear on Railway until they are on `main`.

## When the user wants mobile changes live

1. Prefer the auto-ship path: ensure the work is a PR into **`main`** from `cursor/*`. After Maven verify, CI squash-merges it (unless labeled `hold` / `no-ship`).
2. If auto-ship did not run or failed, land the commits on `main` yourself:
   - `./scripts/ship-mobile-changes.sh` (list)
   - `./scripts/ship-mobile-changes.sh --apply` (cherry-pick + push)
3. Confirm the Actions run: Verify → **Deploy to Railway** (and Cloudflare).
4. Do not tell the user changes are deployed while they only exist on a `cursor/*` branch or an open draft PR.

## When finishing cloud/mobile UI work yourself

- Target **`main`**, not `master`.
- After verify-worthy changes, get them onto `main` (merge/ship) so Railway updates.
- Bump asset / service-worker cache versions when shipping CSS/JS/static UI fixes so clients see the new build.
